<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Bazban</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-11-21 23:28:00</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>You DO NOT have to kill zimbittle to get her to spawn...shes spawns around every 25-45mins and spawns near one of the hands most of the time,then wanders to infront of gukk.Ive heard the worse your faction is with her the better your chance of getting the hoop.I gave her 5 rubies and got no hoops and really bad faction with the bashers,couldn't even train at my guild for awhile.<BR>
The hoop sells for around 6k and is well sought after.<BR>
Only try to get this if you are a DE that isn't worried about your basher faction and are VERY rich.Me being a troll with low chr spends about 161pp on a rubie,a DE enchanter with everything put into chr spends 131pp.<BR>
And thats all i know about it.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kragmire</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-11-22 22:26:31</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Shamans can do this quest a little more efficiently.  Make sure you buff the hell out of your charisma to lower your ruby prices.  You should be able to buy them in the 130-140 plat. range.  Then only buy two rubies at a time.<BR>
<BR>
Why only two?  Because both the Brutechopper and Midnight Mallet are LORE items.  This means that if you do the quest and it awards you a second one of these items, the quest detects that you already have one and you get nothing instead.  You can sell the Chopper and the Mallet to vendors for about 65-70 plat, which cuts the cost of trials about in half.  Of course, you can have a few friends standing by so you can hand items to them when the quest awards them, so you can get around some of the LORE penalty this way.<BR>
<BR>
One last comment; both weapons are LARGE items that will not fit in a backpack.  If you don't have a slot open they will drop on the ground.  Given that Innothule is a swamp with a lot of watery areas, it becomes a real pain if you start dropping 70 plat magic weapons all over the place.<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
